gov.usgs.quakeml.parser

Class QuakeMLConversion

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • gov.usgs.anss.edgethread.EdgeThread
        • gov.usgs.quakeml.parser.QuakeMLConversion
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public final class QuakeMLConversion
extends EdgeThread
    This class is the main for processing data from the database of e-mail messages from the cat2qml table to QuakeML. It uses the catqmlconfig table to get its configuration data for each source, processes open messages for that source, and creates files and store the resulting QuakeML in the cat2qml database.

    Note: the database URL is taked from the property QMLDBServer so this needs to be in the edge.prop where this is run.

    < pre> Configuration table : catqmlconfig varchar(40) - the name of this converstion task source varchar(30) - the name of some organization that sends in picks or bulletins properties text - The properties for processing emails from this source - described below classname varach(40) - The name of the class to instantiate for this conversion (a subclass of QuakeMLHelper) fromre text - The regular expression to use to match the senders email "from" field subjectre text - the regular expression to use to mathe the sends email "subject" field namespace text - This is a list of conversions to use when looking up stations to find their FDSN network codes. Properties (capitalized are mandatory, lower case ones are optional) : Class= The class to instantiate to do the conversion (a subclass of QuakeMLHelper) Agency= The IADRS agency name to pass along Deployment= The IADSR deployment name to pass along NEICAgency= The NEIC agency to pass to Hydra PublicIDStub= This is something like "quakeml:us.anss.org" to put on all public ids DataLimits= The lat long box for stations to be included in the picks format : minlat, maxlat, minlong, maxlong MagLimits= The lat long box for events to be included format : minlat,maxlat, minlong, maxlong preprocessor= Some input is not formed exactly to specs, this is the name of a program to make it be fixed earthmodel= The earthmodel name to put in the origin tag originmethodID= The ID for the origin method to put under the origin tag (AK135?) createauthor= createauthorURI= magmethodID= originmethodID= permittedIR= 5 character permited/expected IR stations names arg Description NO ARGS at this time
